---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Fabric vs. Leather Sofas: Which Best Suits Your Lifestyle?">
  <Navbar />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 bg-zinc-50 min-h-screen">
    <article
      class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 bg-white py-12 md:py-16 shadow-sm border border-zinc-100"
    >
      <!-- Top Image -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <img
          src="/images/article/KURSI RUANG TAMU 1.png"
          alt="Fabric vs. Leather Sofas"
          class="w-full h-[400px] object-cover"
        />
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-8 text-zinc-800 leading-relaxed font-sans px-4 md:px-12"
      >
        <!-- Main Title -->
        <h1
          class="font-display text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] leading-tight mb-6"
        >
          Fabric vs. Leather Sofas: Which Best Suits Your Lifestyle?
        </h1>

        <p>
          Choosing a sofa is more than just selecting a seat; it is a long-term
          investment in the comfort and aesthetics of your living space. At
          Kartika Jaya Ananda Sejahtera, we understand that our customers'
          biggest dilemma often boils down to one question: Fabric or Leather?
        </p>

        <p>
          These two materials offer very different characteristics. To help you
          make the right choice, let's break down the comparison—from durability
          to aesthetics—ensuring it perfectly aligns with your lifestyle.
        </p>

        <!-- Subheading 1 -->
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] mt-10 mb-4">
          Fabric vs. Leather Sofas: Which Best Suits Your Lifestyle?
        </h2>
        <p>
          The longevity of a sofa largely depends on the lifestyle and
          inhabitants of your home.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Fabric Sofas:</strong> Modern materials today, such as performance
          fabrics, offer exceptional resistance to wear and tear. However, fabric
          is generally more susceptible to liquid stains and tends to absorb odors
          (such as cigarette smoke or cooking aromas). If you have pets with sharp
          claws, tightly woven fabrics are usually a safer bet as they do not scratch
          as easily as leather.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Leather Sofas:</strong> Leather is renowned for being an incredibly
          rugged material. It is naturally hypoallergenic—meaning it doesn't harbor
          dust or pet dander—making it the premier choice for allergy sufferers. In
          terms of lifespan, a high-quality leather sofa actually improves in appearance
          as it ages, provided it is treated with a specialized conditioner periodically.
        </p>

        <!-- Side by side images with text -->
        <div
          class="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-center items-center gap-12 my-16"
        >
          <div class="relative flex items-center gap-4">
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span
                class="text-[#6D4C41] font-serif italic mb-2 absolute -left-20 top-10"
                >Fabric Sofas</span
              >
              <!-- Curved arrow svg placeholder -->
              <svg
                class="absolute -left-12 top-16 w-10 h-10 text-[#6D4C41]"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                ><path d="M15 15l4-4m0 0l-4-4m4 4H9a6 6 0 00-6 6v3"></path></svg
              >
            </div>
            <img
              src="/images/article/Mokum Sole Boucle Seasalt _ Mokum Textiles.jpg"
              alt="Fabric Texture"
              class="w-48 h-48 object-cover border border-zinc-200"
            />
          </div>
          <div class="relative flex items-center gap-4">
            <img
              src="/images/article/Bay Harbor Tan Leather Sleeper.jpg"
              alt="Leather Texture"
              class="w-48 h-48 object-cover border border-zinc-200"
            />
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
              <span
                class="text-[#6D4C41] font-serif italic mb-2 absolute -right-24 top-20"
                >Leather Sofas</span
              >
              <!-- Curved arrow svg placeholder -->
              <svg
                class="absolute -right-16 top-10 w-10 h-10 text-[#6D4C41]"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                ><path d="M9 15l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h10a6 6 0 006-6v-3"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Subheading 2 -->
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] mt-10 mb-4">
          Fabric vs. Leather Sofas: Which Best Suits Your Lifestyle?
        </h2>
        <p>
          The visual aspect of a sofa defines the 'soul' of the room it
          inhabits.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Fabric Sofas (Limitless Variety):</strong> If you enjoy exploring
          colors and textures, fabric is the undisputed champion. It is available
          in thousands of patterns, ranging from soft pastels to bold, striking motifs.
          Fabric sofas evoke a warm, cozy, and relaxed atmosphere, making them a perfect
          match for Scandinavian, Bohemian, or Farmhouse interior styles.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Leather Sofas (Luxurious and Timeless):</strong> Leather radiates
          an aura of elegance, professionalism, and luxury. A deep brown leather sofa
          offers a classic, vintage feel, while black or white leather is ideal for
          Modern Minimalist or Industrial styles. Leather automatically elevates the
          visual value of a room, giving it a more exclusive and sophisticated touch.
        </p>

        <!-- Subheading 3 -->
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] mt-10 mb-4">
          Comfort and Maintenance
        </h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Comfort:</strong> Fabric tends to be more temperature-stable—it
          doesn't feel chilly during the rainy season and doesn't stick to the skin
          in hot weather. On the other hand, leather can feel cold when you first
          sit down and may feel slightly "stuffy" if the room lacks proper air circulation.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong>Maintenance:</strong> Leather sofas are exceptionally easy to clean;
          a simple wipe with a damp cloth is usually enough to handle spills. Fabric
          sofas require more attention, such as regular vacuuming and the use of specialized
          cleaners for stubborn stains.
        </p>

        <!-- Staggered Images -->
        <div class="my-16 space-y-12">
          <!-- Image 1 -->
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 justify-start pr-12"
          >
            <img
              src="/images/article/SOFA LOBBY 1.png"
              alt="Luxurious and Timeless"
              class="w-[500px] h-64 object-cover"
            />
            <span
              class="text-[#6D4C41] font-serif italic text-lg font-medium hidden md:block w-48 text-center pt-8"
              >Luxurious and Timeless</span
            >
          </div>
          <!-- Image 2 -->
          <div
            class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 justify-end pl-12"
          >
            <span
              class="text-[#6D4C41] font-serif italic text-lg font-medium hidden md:block w-48 text-center pt-16"
              >Limitless Variety</span
            >
            <img
              src="/images/article/SOFA CUSTOM 2.png"
              alt="Limitless Variety"
              class="w-[400px] h-56 object-cover"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Subheading 4 -->
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] mt-10 mb-4">
          Which One Should You Choose?
        </h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Choose Fabric If:</strong> You prioritize the comfort of soft textures,
          have a flexible budget, and want to perfectly match your sofa's color with
          specific room decor.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Choose Leather If:</strong> You demand ease of cleaning (especially
          if you have young children), are looking for furniture that lasts for decades,
          and want to create a sophisticated, high-class living space.
        </p>

        <!-- Subheading 5 -->
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-[#6D4C41] mt-10 mb-4">
          Find the Best Collection at Kartika Jaya Ananda Sejahtera
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-12">
          Whatever your choice may be, ensure it features a sturdy frame and
          premium materials. Explore our latest collection of fabric and leather
          sofas to find the perfect relaxation partner for your family.
        </p>

        <hr class="border-[#6D4C41]/30 my-8" />

        <p class="font-serif italic text-[#6D4C41] text-sm md:text-base">
          Interested in a further consultation regarding a custom sofa? Contact
          our expert team or visit the Kartika Jaya Ananda Sejahtera showroom
          today!
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
